bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext: I moved our buildvm builders all to the kernel-4.9.3-200.fc25.x86_64 rpm and after a short time many of them started rebooting or failing build jobs. These buildvm's are setup as follows: * They are on rhel7.3 buildvmhosts. * Their storage is an iscsi volume from a netapp, setup on the host as a lvm pv. * Each buildvm has their own lv * There are 32 buildvm's with 8 per buildvmhost (4 buildvmhosts). No errors were seen on the hosts, only the vm's had any issues. I have now moved them back to 4.8.x kernel. I managed to get some output from 2 of them, but much of the other logs were gone due to journald crashing.
